                <p style="line-height: 150%">Betting on boxing matches is a great way to learn about boxers, matches, and the stats involved in determining who is most likely to win a match. While betting on a boxing match and sports in general may seem like a fun sport, it is still important to practice responsible gaming as you would if you were gambling at a casino.
                    Betting online or in a retail casino requires some planning to avoid making decisions that could adversely affect you. This is where responsible gaming comes in, and why it’s important to understand what it actually means.
                </p>

                <h1>What Is Responsible Gaming?</h1>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">Sports betting and gambling are entertaining, but both activities can lead to serious problems when not handled responsibly. Responsible gaming means taking steps before walking into an online casino or sportsbook, such as setting a budget, setting a timer, and understanding that you are playing just for fun.
                    Before engaging in gambling or sports betting, you must understand the organizations you are visiting are designed to win. Understanding this beforehand can help you appreciate small wins and set you up for gaming responsibly.
                    Sports betting for the thrill and exhilaration of placing a bet should be the main reason you bet, rather than as a way to win money.
                </p>

                <h1>Why Is Responsible Gaming Important?</h1>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">Responsible gaming is important because it can keep you from overspending or making decisions that could have adverse consequences. Gambling addiction is a serious problem that needs to be addressed with professional help or a support group.
                    Gambling addiction can have negative consequences like these:</p>
                <ul style="padding-left: 50px; list-style-type: disc; padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px;">
                    <li style="list-style-type: inherit;">Losing money such as savings or important income needed for necessities like rent or mortgage payments</li>
                    <li style="list-style-type: inherit;">Going into severe debt whether that’s through credit card debt or personal loans</li>
                    <li style="list-style-type: inherit;">Keeping secrets from family and friends that will eventually alienate them or cause mistrust </li>
                </ul>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">Responsible gaming means you avoid difficult situations like these.</p>

                <h1>Tips For Practicing Responsible Gaming</h1>
                <h2>Setting A Budget</h2>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">Setting a budget before walking into a sportsbook or casino is helpful in that you can avoid overspending and getting yourself into a precarious situation.
                    Plan a budget before leaving home - come up with a figure that you know you can afford and will not add financial stress or worry, and then stick to that number. It’s important to be strict and not go beyond the agreed upon amount.
                    Also, consider leaving additional credit and debit cards at home.
                </p>
                <h2>Set A Timer</h2>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">Before entering a sportsbook or casino, set a timer on your watch or phone for an allotted time. Once your timer goes off, stop gaming. This is also useful when playing on sportsbook or casino mobile apps.
                    Some mobile apps include timers that will lock you out of the app after you have spent a specified amount of time playing.
                </p>
                <h2>Take Breaks Between Betting Or Gambling</h2>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">If you know you’re going to have a difficult time stopping when your timer goes off, consider playing in short increments.
                    Play for 20 to 30 minutes and take a break. Then get back to it when you have another short window of time. This will help you avoid getting stuck in a routine where you spend hours gaming or betting.
                </p>
                <h2>Enjoy The Small Wins</h2>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">If you can enjoy the thrill of placing a bet or wager instead of just focusing on winning money, you’ll enjoy the experience more and not get bogged down on the outcome. Putting less pressure on yourself to win money can allow you to enjoy the small wins more and approach betting or gambling as a fun pastime rather than a way to generate income. </p>
                <h2>Stop Chasing Losses</h2>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">Chasing losses when gambling means trying to recoup money you have already lost. Chasing losses typically results in losing even more money, so it is seldom a good idea. If you have set a budget before playing, remind yourself to stop if you have lost your budgeted amount. Do not get caught up in the vicious cycle of trying to recoup winnings only to find yourself in greater debt.
                </p>

                <h1>Set Limits On Online Sportsbooks And Casino Apps</h1>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">Any mobile app in the casino or sportsbook industry that is committed to fostering a community of responsible gaming will offer ways to support site or app users.
                    Limiting deposit amounts and capping time spent on the apps are just some of the ways these organizations cultivate responsible gaming.
                    Visit any legal, reputable site and you’ll find a “Responsible Gaming” page.
                </p>

                <h1>Self-Exclusion Programs</h1>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">Self-exclusion is the act of intentionally asking casino and sportsbook operators to add you to a list of banned players in your state. Self-exclusion means you are barred from entering a gambling organization and participating in any gaming activities. While this sounds like an extreme step to take, it’s one that a gambling addict or someone in fear of getting into a negative situation can take to begin getting necessary attention and care.</p>

                <h1>Responsible Gaming At A Glance</h1>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">Responsible gaming is the act of approaching casino gambling and sports betting as a fun pastime or a thrilling and exciting game rather than as a way to “win big.” Setting budgets and time limits are both important ways that a responsible gamer prepares before heading to a casino or sportsbook.
                    Online gambling and sports betting are both safe and enjoyable experiences when conducted at retail casinos or legal online gambling sites; however, it’s imperative that you recognize when you might be making irresponsible decisions and get the necessary attention if needed.</p>

                <h1>National Organizations That Can Help</h1>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">There are some national organizations that can help gambling addicts or anyone who fears they may have a gambling or betting problem. These organizations have proven success stories, and many people who attend meetings have found great support in talking with others. </p>
                <ul style="padding-left: 50px; list-style-type: disc; padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px;">
                    <li style="list-style-type: inherit;"><a href="https://www.gamblersanonymous.org/" target="_blank" style="color: #346896; text-decoration: underline;">Gambler Anonymous</a> - This is a national organization that has local chapters around the country. It’s free to join and there are no membership fees. They have been helping people since 1957.
                    </li>
                    <li style="list-style-type: inherit;"><a href="https://www.ncpgambling.org/" target="_blank" style="color: #346896; text-decoration: underline;">National Council for Problem Gambling</a> - This is also a national organization that offers treatment and recovery services and increases awareness of responsible gaming. Visit the website to find a chapter near you.
                    </li>
                    <li style="list-style-type: inherit;"><a href="https://www.nfcc.org/" target="_blank" style="color: #346896; text-decoration: underline;">The National Foundation for Credit Card Counseling</a> - This organization helps individuals who find themselves in credit card debt and need help.</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">These organizations are all nationally recognized and offer resources to help you if you find yourself with a gambling addiction or are feeling overwhelmed with a gambling problem. Do not hesitate to get in touch with one of the above contacts should you need it. </p>

                <h1>If You Have A Problem With Gambling</h1>
                <p style="line-height: 150%">If you believe you might be addicted to gambling or have gotten yourself into debt or trouble because of gambling, it’s crucial that you seek help. Problems that arise from a gambling addiction do not go away on their own.
                    It’s critical that you address your problems and begin the steps needed to stop the gambling and assess the problems that have arisen as a result.
                    <a href="https://www.gamblersanonymous.org/ga/hotlines" target="_blank" style="color: #346896; text-decoration: underline;">Visit this page</a> at Gamblers Anonymous to find the hotline for your state.
                </p>

